28/** \internal \returns b if a<=0, and returns a otherwise. */
29inline std::ptrdiff_t manage_caching_sizes_helper(std::ptrdiff_t a, std::ptrdiff_t b)
30{
31 return a<=0 ? b : a;

70/** \internal */
71struct CacheSizes {
72 CacheSizes(): m_l1(-1),m_l2(-1),m_l3(-1) {
73 int l1CacheSize, l2CacheSize, l3CacheSize;
74 queryCacheSizes(l1CacheSize, l2CacheSize, l3CacheSize);
75 m_l1 = manage_caching_sizes_helper(l1CacheSize, defaultL1CacheSize);
76 m_l2 = manage_caching_sizes_helper(l2CacheSize, defaultL2CacheSize);
77 m_l3 = manage_caching_sizes_helper(l3CacheSize, defaultL3CacheSize);
78 }
79
80 std::ptrdiff_t m_l1;
81 std::ptrdiff_t m_l2;
82 std::ptrdiff_t m_l3;
83};
84
85/** \internal */
86inline void manage_caching_sizes(Action action, std::ptrdiff_t* l1, std::ptrdiff_t* l2, std::ptrdiff_t* l3)
87{
88 static CacheSizes m_cacheSizes;
89
90 if(action==SetAction)
91 {
92 // set the cpu cache size and cache all block sizes from a global cache size in byte
93 eigen_internal_assert(l1!=0 && l2!=0);
94 m_cacheSizes.m_l1 = *l1;
95 m_cacheSizes.m_l2 = *l2;
96 m_cacheSizes.m_l3 = *l3;
97 }
98 else if(action==GetAction)
99 {
100 eigen_internal_assert(l1!=0 && l2!=0);
101 *l1 = m_cacheSizes.m_l1;
102 *l2 = m_cacheSizes.m_l2;
103 *l3 = m_cacheSizes.m_l3;
104 }
105 else
106 {
107 eigen_internal_assert(false);
108 }
109}

111/* Helper for computeProductBlockingSizes.
112 *
113 * Given a m x k times k x n matrix product of scalar types \c LhsScalar and \c RhsScalar,
114 * this function computes the blocking size parameters along the respective dimensions
115 * for matrix products and related algorithms. The blocking sizes depends on various
116 * parameters:
117 * - the L1 and L2 cache sizes,
118 * - the register level blocking sizes defined by gebp_traits,
119 * - the number of scalars that fit into a packet (when vectorization is enabled).
120 *
121 * \sa setCpuCacheSizes */
122
123template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, int KcFactor, typename Index>
124void evaluateProductBlockingSizesHeuristic(Index& k, Index& m, Index& n, Index num_threads = 1)
125{
126 typedef gebp_traits<LhsScalar,RhsScalar> Traits;
127
128 // Explanations:
129 // Let's recall that the product algorithms form mc x kc vertical panels A' on the lhs and
130 // kc x nc blocks B' on the rhs. B' has to fit into L2/L3 cache. Moreover, A' is processed
131 // per mr x kc horizontal small panels where mr is the blocking size along the m dimension
132 // at the register level. This small horizontal panel has to stay within L1 cache.
133 std::ptrdiff_t l1, l2, l3;
134 manage_caching_sizes(GetAction, &l1, &l2, &l3);
135 #ifdef EIGEN_VECTORIZE_AVX512
136 // We need to find a rationale for that, but without this adjustment,
137 // performance with AVX512 is pretty bad, like -20% slower.
138 // One reason is that with increasing packet-size, the blocking size k
139 // has to become pretty small if we want that 1 lhs panel fit within L1.
140 // For instance, with the 3pX4 kernel and double, the size of the lhs+rhs panels are:
141 // k*(3*64 + 4*8) Bytes, with l1=32kBytes, and k%8=0, we have k=144.
142 // This is quite small for a good reuse of the accumulation registers.
143 l1 *= 4;
144 #endif
145
146 if (num_threads > 1) {
147 typedef typename Traits::ResScalar ResScalar;
148 enum {
149 kdiv = KcFactor * (Traits::mr * sizeof(LhsScalar) + Traits::nr * sizeof(RhsScalar)),
150 ksub = Traits::mr * Traits::nr * sizeof(ResScalar),
151 kr = 8,
152 mr = Traits::mr,
153 nr = Traits::nr
154 };
155 // Increasing k gives us more time to prefetch the content of the "C"
156 // registers. However once the latency is hidden there is no point in
157 // increasing the value of k, so we'll cap it at 320 (value determined
158 // experimentally).
159 const Index k_cache = (numext::mini<Index>)((l1-ksub)/kdiv, 320);
160 if (k_cache < k) {
161 k = k_cache - (k_cache % kr);
162 eigen_internal_assert(k > 0);
163 }
164
165 const Index n_cache = (l2-l1) / (nr * sizeof(RhsScalar) * k);
166 const Index n_per_thread = numext::div_ceil(n, num_threads);
167 if (n_cache <= n_per_thread) {
168 // Don't exceed the capacity of the l2 cache.
169 eigen_internal_assert(n_cache >= static_cast<Index>(nr));
170 n = n_cache - (n_cache % nr);
171 eigen_internal_assert(n > 0);
172 } else {
173 n = (numext::mini<Index>)(n, (n_per_thread + nr - 1) - ((n_per_thread + nr - 1) % nr));
174 }
175
176 if (l3 > l2) {
177 // l3 is shared between all cores, so we'll give each thread its own chunk of l3.
178 const Index m_cache = (l3-l2) / (sizeof(LhsScalar) * k * num_threads);
179 const Index m_per_thread = numext::div_ceil(m, num_threads);
180 if(m_cache < m_per_thread && m_cache >= static_cast<Index>(mr)) {
181 m = m_cache - (m_cache % mr);
182 eigen_internal_assert(m > 0);
183 } else {
184 m = (numext::mini<Index>)(m, (m_per_thread + mr - 1) - ((m_per_thread + mr - 1) % mr));
185 }
186 }
187 }
188 else {
189 // In unit tests we do not want to use extra large matrices,
190 // so we reduce the cache size to check the blocking strategy is not flawed
191#ifdef EIGEN_DEBUG_SMALL_PRODUCT_BLOCKS
192 l1 = 9*1024;
193 l2 = 32*1024;
194 l3 = 512*1024;
195#endif
196
197 // Early return for small problems because the computation below are time consuming for small problems.
198 // Perhaps it would make more sense to consider k*n*m??
199 // Note that for very tiny problem, this function should be bypassed anyway
200 // because we use the coefficient-based implementation for them.
201 if((numext::maxi)(k,(numext::maxi)(m,n))<48)
202 return;
203
204 typedef typename Traits::ResScalar ResScalar;
205 enum {
206 k_peeling = 8,
207 k_div = KcFactor * (Traits::mr * sizeof(LhsScalar) + Traits::nr * sizeof(RhsScalar)),
208 k_sub = Traits::mr * Traits::nr * sizeof(ResScalar)
209 };
210
211 // ---- 1st level of blocking on L1, yields kc ----
212
213 // Blocking on the third dimension (i.e., k) is chosen so that an horizontal panel
214 // of size mr x kc of the lhs plus a vertical panel of kc x nr of the rhs both fits within L1 cache.
215 // We also include a register-level block of the result (mx x nr).
216 // (In an ideal world only the lhs panel would stay in L1)
217 // Moreover, kc has to be a multiple of 8 to be compatible with loop peeling, leading to a maximum blocking size of:
218 const Index max_kc = numext::maxi<Index>(((l1-k_sub)/k_div) & (~(k_peeling-1)),1);
219 const Index old_k = k;
220 if(k>max_kc)
221 {
222 // We are really blocking on the third dimension:
223 // -> reduce blocking size to make sure the last block is as large as possible
224 // while keeping the same number of sweeps over the result.
225 k = (k%max_kc)==0 ? max_kc
226 : max_kc - k_peeling * ((max_kc-1-(k%max_kc))/(k_peeling*(k/max_kc+1)));
227
228 eigen_internal_assert(((old_k/k) == (old_k/max_kc)) && "the number of sweeps has to remain the same");
229 }
230
231 // ---- 2nd level of blocking on max(L2,L3), yields nc ----
232
233 // TODO find a reliable way to get the actual amount of cache per core to use for 2nd level blocking, that is:
234 // actual_l2 = max(l2, l3/nb_core_sharing_l3)
235 // The number below is quite conservative: it is better to underestimate the cache size rather than overestimating it)
236 // For instance, it corresponds to 6MB of L3 shared among 4 cores.
237 #ifdef EIGEN_DEBUG_SMALL_PRODUCT_BLOCKS
238 const Index actual_l2 = l3;
239 #else
240 const Index actual_l2 = 1572864; // == 1.5 MB
241 #endif
242
243 // Here, nc is chosen such that a block of kc x nc of the rhs fit within half of L2.
244 // The second half is implicitly reserved to access the result and lhs coefficients.
245 // When k<max_kc, then nc can arbitrarily growth. In practice, it seems to be fruitful
246 // to limit this growth: we bound nc to growth by a factor x1.5.
247 // However, if the entire lhs block fit within L1, then we are not going to block on the rows at all,
248 // and it becomes fruitful to keep the packed rhs blocks in L1 if there is enough remaining space.
249 Index max_nc;
250 const Index lhs_bytes = m * k * sizeof(LhsScalar);
251 const Index remaining_l1 = l1- k_sub - lhs_bytes;
252 if(remaining_l1 >= Index(Traits::nr*sizeof(RhsScalar))*k)
253 {
254 // L1 blocking
255 max_nc = remaining_l1 / (k*sizeof(RhsScalar));
256 }
257 else
258 {
259 // L2 blocking
260 max_nc = (3*actual_l2)/(2*2*max_kc*sizeof(RhsScalar));
261 }
262 // WARNING Below, we assume that Traits::nr is a power of two.
263 Index nc = numext::mini<Index>(actual_l2/(2*k*sizeof(RhsScalar)), max_nc) & (~(Traits::nr-1));
264 if(n>nc)
265 {
266 // We are really blocking over the columns:
267 // -> reduce blocking size to make sure the last block is as large as possible
268 // while keeping the same number of sweeps over the packed lhs.
269 // Here we allow one more sweep if this gives us a perfect match, thus the commented "-1"
270 n = (n%nc)==0 ? nc
271 : (nc - Traits::nr * ((nc/*-1*/-(n%nc))/(Traits::nr*(n/nc+1))));
272 }
273 else if(old_k==k)
274 {
275 // So far, no blocking at all, i.e., kc==k, and nc==n.
276 // In this case, let's perform a blocking over the rows such that the packed lhs data is kept in cache L1/L2
277 // TODO: part of this blocking strategy is now implemented within the kernel itself, so the L1-based heuristic here should be obsolete.
278 Index problem_size = k*n*sizeof(LhsScalar);
279 Index actual_lm = actual_l2;
280 Index max_mc = m;
281 if(problem_size<=1024)
282 {
283 // problem is small enough to keep in L1
284 // Let's choose m such that lhs's block fit in 1/3 of L1
285 actual_lm = l1;
286 }
287 else if(l3!=0 && problem_size<=32768)
288 {
289 // we have both L2 and L3, and problem is small enough to be kept in L2
290 // Let's choose m such that lhs's block fit in 1/3 of L2
291 actual_lm = l2;
292 max_mc = (numext::mini<Index>)(576,max_mc);
293 }
294 Index mc = (numext::mini<Index>)(actual_lm/(3*k*sizeof(LhsScalar)), max_mc);
295 if (mc > Traits::mr) mc -= mc % Traits::mr;
296 else if (mc==0) return;
297 m = (m%mc)==0 ? mc
298 : (mc - Traits::mr * ((mc/*-1*/-(m%mc))/(Traits::mr*(m/mc+1))));
299 }
300 }
301}
302
303template <typename Index>
304inline bool useSpecificBlockingSizes(Index& k, Index& m, Index& n)
305{
306#ifdef EIGEN_TEST_SPECIFIC_BLOCKING_SIZES
307 if (EIGEN_TEST_SPECIFIC_BLOCKING_SIZES) {
308 k = numext::mini<Index>(k, EIGEN_TEST_SPECIFIC_BLOCKING_SIZE_K);
309 m = numext::mini<Index>(m, EIGEN_TEST_SPECIFIC_BLOCKING_SIZE_M);
310 n = numext::mini<Index>(n, EIGEN_TEST_SPECIFIC_BLOCKING_SIZE_N);
311 return true;
312 }
313#else
314 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(k)
315 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(m)
316 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(n)
317#endif
318 return false;
319}

321/** \brief Computes the blocking parameters for a m x k times k x n matrix product
322 *
323 * \param[in,out] k Input: the third dimension of the product. Output: the blocking size along the same dimension.
324 * \param[in,out] m Input: the number of rows of the left hand side. Output: the blocking size along the same dimension.
325 * \param[in,out] n Input: the number of columns of the right hand side. Output: the blocking size along the same dimension.
326 *
327 * Given a m x k times k x n matrix product of scalar types \c LhsScalar and \c RhsScalar,
328 * this function computes the blocking size parameters along the respective dimensions
329 * for matrix products and related algorithms.
330 *
331 * The blocking size parameters may be evaluated:
332 * - either by a heuristic based on cache sizes;
333 * - or using fixed prescribed values (for testing purposes).
334 *
335 * \sa setCpuCacheSizes */
336
337template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, int KcFactor, typename Index>
338void computeProductBlockingSizes(Index& k, Index& m, Index& n, Index num_threads = 1)
339{
340 if (!useSpecificBlockingSizes(k, m, n)) {
341 evaluateProductBlockingSizesHeuristic<LhsScalar, RhsScalar, KcFactor, Index>(k, m, n, num_threads);
342 }
343}
344
345template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename Index>
346inline void computeProductBlockingSizes(Index& k, Index& m, Index& n, Index num_threads = 1)
347{
348 computeProductBlockingSizes<LhsScalar,RhsScalar,1,Index>(k, m, n, num_threads);
349}

365 EIGEN_ALWAYS_INLINE static void run(const CJ& cj, T& a, T& b, T& c, T& t)

367 t = b; t = cj.pmul(a,t); c = padd(c,t);

375 }

436/* Vectorization logic
437 * real*real: unpack rhs to constant packets, ...
438 *
439 * cd*cd : unpack rhs to (b_r,b_r), (b_i,b_i), mul to get (a_r b_r,a_i b_r) (a_r b_i,a_i b_i),
440 * storing each res packet into two packets (2x2),
441 * at the end combine them: swap the second and addsub them
442 * cf*cf : same but with 2x4 blocks
443 * cplx*real : unpack rhs to constant packets, ...
444 * real*cplx : load lhs as (a0,a0,a1,a1), and mul as usual
445 */
446template<typename _LhsScalar, typename _RhsScalar, bool _ConjLhs, bool _ConjRhs, int Arch, int _PacketSize>
447class gebp_traits
448{
449public:
450 typedef _LhsScalar LhsScalar;
451 typedef _RhsScalar RhsScalar;
452 typedef typename ScalarBinaryOpTraits<LhsScalar, RhsScalar>::ReturnType ResScalar;
453
454 PACKET_DECL_COND_PREFIX(_, Lhs, _PacketSize);
455 PACKET_DECL_COND_PREFIX(_, Rhs, _PacketSize);
456 PACKET_DECL_COND_PREFIX(_, Res, _PacketSize);
457
458 enum {
459 ConjLhs = _ConjLhs,
460 ConjRhs = _ConjRhs,
461 Vectorizable = unpacket_traits<_LhsPacket>::vectorizable && unpacket_traits<_RhsPacket>::vectorizable,
462 LhsPacketSize = Vectorizable ? unpacket_traits<_LhsPacket>::size : 1,
463 RhsPacketSize = Vectorizable ? unpacket_traits<_RhsPacket>::size : 1,
464 ResPacketSize = Vectorizable ? unpacket_traits<_ResPacket>::size : 1,
465
466 NumberOfRegisters = EIGEN_ARCH_DEFAULT_NUMBER_OF_REGISTERS,
467
468 // register block size along the N direction must be 1 or 4
469 nr = 4,
470
471 // register block size along the M direction (currently, this one cannot be modified)
472 default_mr = (EIGEN_PLAIN_ENUM_MIN(16,NumberOfRegisters)/2/nr)*LhsPacketSize,
473#if defined(EIGEN_HAS_SINGLE_INSTRUCTION_MADD) && !defined(EIGEN_VECTORIZE_ALTIVEC) && !defined(EIGEN_VECTORIZE_VSX) \
474 && ((!EIGEN_COMP_MSVC) || (EIGEN_COMP_MSVC>=1914))
475 // we assume 16 registers or more
476 // See bug 992, if the scalar type is not vectorizable but that EIGEN_HAS_SINGLE_INSTRUCTION_MADD is defined,
477 // then using 3*LhsPacketSize triggers non-implemented paths in syrk.
478 // Bug 1515: MSVC prior to v19.14 yields to register spilling.
479 mr = Vectorizable ? 3*LhsPacketSize : default_mr,
480#else
481 mr = default_mr,
482#endif
483
484 LhsProgress = LhsPacketSize,
485 RhsProgress = 1
486 };

540 template<typename LhsPacketType, typename RhsPacketType, typename AccPacketType, typename LaneIdType>
541 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void madd(const LhsPacketType& a, const RhsPacketType& b, AccPacketType& c, RhsPacketType& tmp, const LaneIdType&) const
542 {
543 conj_helper<LhsPacketType,RhsPacketType,ConjLhs,ConjRhs> cj;
544 // It would be a lot cleaner to call pmadd all the time. Unfortunately if we
545 // let gcc allocate the register in which to store the result of the pmul
546 // (in the case where there is no FMA) gcc fails to figure out how to avoid
547 // spilling register.
548#ifdef EIGEN_HAS_SINGLE_INSTRUCTION_MADD
549 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(tmp);
550 c = cj.pmadd(a,b,c);
551#else
552 tmp = b; tmp = cj.pmul(a,tmp); c = padd(c,tmp);
553#endif
554 }
555
556 template<typename LhsPacketType, typename AccPacketType, typename LaneIdType>
557 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void madd(const LhsPacketType& a, const RhsPacketx4& b, AccPacketType& c, RhsPacket& tmp, const LaneIdType& lane) const
558 {
559 madd(a, b.get(lane), c, tmp, lane);
560 }
561
562 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void acc(const AccPacket& c, const ResPacket& alpha, ResPacket& r) const
563 {
564 r = pmadd(c,alpha,r);
565 }
566
567 template<typename ResPacketHalf>
568 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void acc(const ResPacketHalf& c, const ResPacketHalf& alpha, ResPacketHalf& r) const
569 {
570 r = pmadd(c,alpha,r);
571 }
572
573};

710template<typename Packet>
711struct DoublePacket
712{
713 Packet first;
714 Packet second;
715};
716
717template<typename Packet>
718DoublePacket<Packet> padd(const DoublePacket<Packet> &a, const DoublePacket<Packet> &b)
719{
720 DoublePacket<Packet> res;
721 res.first = padd(a.first, b.first);
722 res.second = padd(a.second,b.second);
723 return res;
724}

726// note that for DoublePacket<RealPacket> the "4" in "downto4"
727// corresponds to the number of complexes, so it means "8"
728// it terms of real coefficients.
729
730template<typename Packet>
731const DoublePacket<Packet>&
732predux_half_dowto4(const DoublePacket<Packet> &a,
733 typename enable_if<unpacket_traits<Packet>::size<=8>::type* = 0)
734{
735 return a;
736}
737
738template<typename Packet>
739DoublePacket<typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half>
740predux_half_dowto4(const DoublePacket<Packet> &a,
741 typename enable_if<unpacket_traits<Packet>::size==16>::type* = 0)
742{
743 // yes, that's pretty hackish :(
744 DoublePacket<typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half> res;
745 typedef std::complex<typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::type> Cplx;
746 typedef typename packet_traits<Cplx>::type CplxPacket;
747 res.first = predux_half_dowto4(CplxPacket(a.first)).v;
748 res.second = predux_half_dowto4(CplxPacket(a.second)).v;
749 return res;
750}

752// same here, "quad" actually means "8" in terms of real coefficients
753template<typename Scalar, typename RealPacket>
754void loadQuadToDoublePacket(const Scalar* b, DoublePacket<RealPacket>& dest,
755 typename enable_if<unpacket_traits<RealPacket>::size<=8>::type* = 0)
756{
757 dest.first = pset1<RealPacket>(numext::real(*b));
758 dest.second = pset1<RealPacket>(numext::imag(*b));
759}
760
761template<typename Scalar, typename RealPacket>
762void loadQuadToDoublePacket(const Scalar* b, DoublePacket<RealPacket>& dest,
763 typename enable_if<unpacket_traits<RealPacket>::size==16>::type* = 0)
764{
765 // yes, that's pretty hackish too :(
766 typedef typename NumTraits<Scalar>::Real RealScalar;
767 RealScalar r[4] = {numext::real(b[0]), numext::real(b[0]), numext::real(b[1]), numext::real(b[1])};
768 RealScalar i[4] = {numext::imag(b[0]), numext::imag(b[0]), numext::imag(b[1]), numext::imag(b[1])};
769 dest.first = ploadquad<RealPacket>(r);
770 dest.second = ploadquad<RealPacket>(i);
771}

900 {

913 {
914 madd(a, b.get(lane), c, tmp, lane);
915 }

917 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void acc(const Scalar& c, const Scalar& alpha, Scalar& r) const { r += alpha * c; }
918
919 template<typename RealPacketType, typename ResPacketType>
920 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void acc(const DoublePacket<RealPacketType>& c, const ResPacketType& alpha, ResPacketType& r) const
921 {
922 // assemble c
923 ResPacketType tmp;
924 if((!ConjLhs)&&(!ConjRhs))
925 {
926 tmp = pcplxflip(pconj(ResPacketType(c.second)));
927 tmp = padd(ResPacketType(c.first),tmp);
928 }
929 else if((!ConjLhs)&&(ConjRhs))
930 {
931 tmp = pconj(pcplxflip(ResPacketType(c.second)));
932 tmp = padd(ResPacketType(c.first),tmp);
933 }
934 else if((ConjLhs)&&(!ConjRhs))
935 {
936 tmp = pcplxflip(ResPacketType(c.second));
937 tmp = padd(pconj(ResPacketType(c.first)),tmp);
938 }
939 else if((ConjLhs)&&(ConjRhs))
940 {
941 tmp = pcplxflip(ResPacketType(c.second));
942 tmp = psub(pconj(ResPacketType(c.first)),tmp);
943 }
944
945 r = pmadd(tmp,alpha,r);
946 }
947
948protected:
949 conj_helper<LhsScalar,RhsScalar,ConjLhs,ConjRhs> cj;
950};

1126 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void madd(const LhsPacket& a, const RhsPacketx4& b, AccPacket& c, RhsPacket& /*tmp*/, const FixedInt<3>&) const
1127 { madd_helper<3>(a, b, c); }
1128
1129 private:
1130 template<int LaneID>
1131 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void madd_helper(const LhsPacket& a, const RhsPacketx4& b, AccPacket& c) const
1132 {
1133 #if EIGEN_COMP_GNUC_STRICT && !(EIGEN_GNUC_AT_LEAST(9,0))
1134 // workaround gcc issue https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=89101
1135 // vfmaq_laneq_f32 is implemented through a costly dup
1136 if(LaneID==0) asm("fmla %0.4s, %1.4s, %2.s[0]\n" : "+w" (c) : "w" (a), "w" (b) : );
1137 else if(LaneID==1) asm("fmla %0.4s, %1.4s, %2.s[1]\n" : "+w" (c) : "w" (a), "w" (b) : );
1138 else if(LaneID==2) asm("fmla %0.4s, %1.4s, %2.s[2]\n" : "+w" (c) : "w" (a), "w" (b) : );
1139 else if(LaneID==3) asm("fmla %0.4s, %1.4s, %2.s[3]\n" : "+w" (c) : "w" (a), "w" (b) : );
1140 #else
1141 c = vfmaq_laneq_f32(c, a, b, LaneID);
1142 #endif
1143 }

1220/* optimized General packed Block * packed Panel product kernel
1221 *
1222 * Mixing type logic: C += A * B
1223 * | A | B | comments
1224 * |real |cplx | no vectorization yet, would require to pack A with duplication
1225 * |cplx |real | easy vectorization

1227template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>

1236 typedef typename Traits::RhsPacket RhsPacket;

1238 typedef typename Traits::AccPacket AccPacket;
1239 typedef typename Traits::RhsPacketx4 RhsPacketx4;
1240
1241 typedef typename RhsPanelHelper<RhsPacket, RhsPacketx4, 15>::type RhsPanel15;

1244

1246 typedef typename SwappedTraits::LhsPacket SLhsPacket;

1311template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
1312struct last_row_process_16_packets<LhsScalar, RhsScalar, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs, 16> {
1313 typedef gebp_traits<LhsScalar,RhsScalar,ConjugateLhs,ConjugateRhs,Architecture::Target> Traits;
1314 typedef gebp_traits<RhsScalar,LhsScalar,ConjugateRhs,ConjugateLhs,Architecture::Target> SwappedTraits;
1315
1316 typedef typename Traits::ResScalar ResScalar;
1317 typedef typename SwappedTraits::LhsPacket SLhsPacket;
1318 typedef typename SwappedTraits::RhsPacket SRhsPacket;
1319 typedef typename SwappedTraits::ResPacket SResPacket;
1320 typedef typename SwappedTraits::AccPacket SAccPacket;
1321
1322 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void operator()(const DataMapper& res, SwappedTraits &straits, const LhsScalar* blA,
1323 const RhsScalar* blB, Index depth, const Index endk, Index i, Index j2,
1324 ResScalar alpha, SAccPacket &C0)
1325 {
1326 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SResPacket>::half>::half SResPacketQuarter;
1327 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SLhsPacket>::half>::half SLhsPacketQuarter;
1328 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SRhsPacket>::half>::half SRhsPacketQuarter;
1329 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SAccPacket>::half>::half SAccPacketQuarter;
1330
1331 SResPacketQuarter R = res.template gatherPacket<SResPacketQuarter>(i, j2);
1332 SResPacketQuarter alphav = pset1<SResPacketQuarter>(alpha);
1333
1334 if (depth - endk > 0)
1335 {
1336 // We have to handle the last row(s) of the rhs, which
1337 // correspond to a half-packet
1338 SAccPacketQuarter c0 = predux_half_dowto4(predux_half_dowto4(C0));
1339
1340 for (Index kk = endk; kk < depth; kk++)
1341 {
1342 SLhsPacketQuarter a0;
1343 SRhsPacketQuarter b0;
1344 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB, a0);
1345 straits.loadRhs(blA, b0);
1346 straits.madd(a0,b0,c0,b0, fix<0>);
1347 blB += SwappedTraits::LhsProgress/4;
1348 blA += 1;
1349 }
1350 straits.acc(c0, alphav, R);
1351 }
1352 else
1353 {
1354 straits.acc(predux_half_dowto4(predux_half_dowto4(C0)), alphav, R);
1355 }
1356 res.scatterPacket(i, j2, R);
1357 }
1358};

1360template<int nr, Index LhsProgress, Index RhsProgress, typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename ResScalar, typename AccPacket, typename LhsPacket, typename RhsPacket, typename ResPacket, typename GEBPTraits, typename LinearMapper, typename DataMapper>
1361struct lhs_process_one_packet
1362{
1363 typedef typename GEBPTraits::RhsPacketx4 RhsPacketx4;
1364
1365 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void peeled_kc_onestep(Index K, const LhsScalar* blA, const RhsScalar* blB, GEBPTraits traits, LhsPacket *A0, RhsPacketx4 *rhs_panel, RhsPacket *T0, AccPacket *C0, AccPacket *C1, AccPacket *C2, AccPacket *C3)
1366 {
1367 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 1X4");
1368 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!");
1369 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(0+1*K)*LhsProgress], *A0);
1370 traits.loadRhs(&blB[(0+4*K)*RhsProgress], *rhs_panel);
1371 traits.madd(*A0, *rhs_panel, *C0, *T0, fix<0>);
1372 traits.madd(*A0, *rhs_panel, *C1, *T0, fix<1>);
1373 traits.madd(*A0, *rhs_panel, *C2, *T0, fix<2>);
1374 traits.madd(*A0, *rhs_panel, *C3, *T0, fix<3>);
1375 #if EIGEN_GNUC_AT_LEAST(6,0) && defined(EIGEN_VECTORIZE_SSE)
1376 __asm__ ("" : "+x,m" (*A0));
1377 #endif
1378 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 1X4");
1379 }
1380
1381 EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void operator()(
1382 const DataMapper& res, const LhsScalar* blockA, const RhsScalar* blockB, ResScalar alpha,
1383 Index peelStart, Index peelEnd, Index strideA, Index strideB, Index offsetA, Index offsetB,
1384 int prefetch_res_offset, Index peeled_kc, Index pk, Index cols, Index depth, Index packet_cols4)
1385 {
1386 GEBPTraits traits;
1387
1388 // loops on each largest micro horizontal panel of lhs
1389 // (LhsProgress x depth)
1390 for(Index i=peelStart; i<peelEnd; i+=LhsProgress)
1391 {
1392 // loops on each largest micro vertical panel of rhs (depth * nr)
1393 for(Index j2=0; j2<packet_cols4; j2+=nr)
1394 {
1395 // We select a LhsProgress x nr micro block of res
1396 // which is entirely stored into 1 x nr registers.
1397
1398 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(LhsProgress)];
1399 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1400
1401 // gets res block as register
1402 AccPacket C0, C1, C2, C3;
1403 traits.initAcc(C0);
1404 traits.initAcc(C1);
1405 traits.initAcc(C2);
1406 traits.initAcc(C3);
1407 // To improve instruction pipelining, let's double the accumulation registers:
1408 // even k will accumulate in C*, while odd k will accumulate in D*.
1409 // This trick is crutial to get good performance with FMA, otherwise it is
1410 // actually faster to perform separated MUL+ADD because of a naturally
1411 // better instruction-level parallelism.
1412 AccPacket D0, D1, D2, D3;
1413 traits.initAcc(D0);
1414 traits.initAcc(D1);
1415 traits.initAcc(D2);
1416 traits.initAcc(D3);
1417
1418 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 0);
1419 LinearMapper r1 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 1);
1420 LinearMapper r2 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 2);
1421 LinearMapper r3 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 3);
1422
1423 r0.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1424 r1.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1425 r2.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1426 r3.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1427
1428 // performs "inner" products
1429 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB*nr];
1430 prefetch(&blB[0]);
1431 LhsPacket A0, A1;
1432
1433 for(Index k=0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
1434 {
1435 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX4");
1436 RhsPacketx4 rhs_panel;
1437 RhsPacket T0;
1438
1439 internal::prefetch(blB+(48+0));
1440 peeled_kc_onestep(0, blA, blB, traits, &A0, &rhs_panel, &T0, &C0, &C1, &C2, &C3);
1441 peeled_kc_onestep(1, blA, blB, traits, &A1, &rhs_panel, &T0, &D0, &D1, &D2, &D3);
1442 peeled_kc_onestep(2, blA, blB, traits, &A0, &rhs_panel, &T0, &C0, &C1, &C2, &C3);
1443 peeled_kc_onestep(3, blA, blB, traits, &A1, &rhs_panel, &T0, &D0, &D1, &D2, &D3);
1444 internal::prefetch(blB+(48+16));
1445 peeled_kc_onestep(4, blA, blB, traits, &A0, &rhs_panel, &T0, &C0, &C1, &C2, &C3);
1446 peeled_kc_onestep(5, blA, blB, traits, &A1, &rhs_panel, &T0, &D0, &D1, &D2, &D3);
1447 peeled_kc_onestep(6, blA, blB, traits, &A0, &rhs_panel, &T0, &C0, &C1, &C2, &C3);
1448 peeled_kc_onestep(7, blA, blB, traits, &A1, &rhs_panel, &T0, &D0, &D1, &D2, &D3);
1449
1450 blB += pk*4*RhsProgress;
1451 blA += pk*LhsProgress;
1452
1453 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX4");
1454 }
1455 C0 = padd(C0,D0);
1456 C1 = padd(C1,D1);
1457 C2 = padd(C2,D2);
1458 C3 = padd(C3,D3);
1459
1460 // process remaining peeled loop
1461 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
1462 {
1463 RhsPacketx4 rhs_panel;
1464 RhsPacket T0;
1465 peeled_kc_onestep(0, blA, blB, traits, &A0, &rhs_panel, &T0, &C0, &C1, &C2, &C3);
1466 blB += 4*RhsProgress;
1467 blA += LhsProgress;
1468 }
1469
1470 ResPacket R0, R1;
1471 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
1472
1473 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0);
1474 R1 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0);
1475 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
1476 traits.acc(C1, alphav, R1);
1477 r0.storePacket(0, R0);
1478 r1.storePacket(0, R1);
1479
1480 R0 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0);
1481 R1 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0);
1482 traits.acc(C2, alphav, R0);
1483 traits.acc(C3, alphav, R1);
1484 r2.storePacket(0, R0);
1485 r3.storePacket(0, R1);
1486 }
1487
1488 // Deal with remaining columns of the rhs
1489 for(Index j2=packet_cols4; j2<cols; j2++)
1490 {
1491 // One column at a time
1492 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(LhsProgress)];
1493 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1494
1495 // gets res block as register
1496 AccPacket C0;
1497 traits.initAcc(C0);
1498
1499 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2);
1500
1501 // performs "inner" products
1502 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB];
1503 LhsPacket A0;
1504
1505 for(Index k= 0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
1506 {
1507 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX1");
1508 RhsPacket B_0;
1509
1510#define EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(K) \
1511 do { \
1512 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX1"); \
1513 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!"); \
1514 /* FIXME: why unaligned???? */ \
1515 traits.loadLhsUnaligned(&blA[(0+1*K)*LhsProgress], A0); \
1516 traits.loadRhs(&blB[(0+K)*RhsProgress], B_0); \
1517 traits.madd(A0, B_0, C0, B_0, fix<0>); \
1518 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX1"); \
1519 } while(false);
1520
1521 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1522 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(1);
1523 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(2);
1524 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(3);
1525 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(4);
1526 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(5);
1527 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(6);
1528 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(7);
1529
1530 blB += pk*RhsProgress;
1531 blA += pk*LhsProgress;
1532
1533 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 1/half/quarterX1");
1534 }
1535
1536 // process remaining peeled loop
1537 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
1538 {
1539 RhsPacket B_0;
1540 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1541 blB += RhsProgress;
1542 blA += LhsProgress;
1543 }
1544#undef EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP
1545 ResPacket R0;
1546 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
1547 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0);
1548 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
1549 r0.storePacket(0, R0);
1550 }
1551 }
1552 }
1553};
1554
1555template<int nr, Index LhsProgress, Index RhsProgress, typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename ResScalar, typename AccPacket, typename LhsPacket, typename RhsPacket, typename ResPacket, typename GEBPTraits, typename LinearMapper, typename DataMapper>
1556struct lhs_process_fraction_of_packet : lhs_process_one_packet<nr, LhsProgress, RhsProgress, LhsScalar, RhsScalar, ResScalar, AccPacket, LhsPacket, RhsPacket, ResPacket, GEBPTraits, LinearMapper, DataMapper>
1557{
1558
1559EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE void peeled_kc_onestep(Index K, const LhsScalar* blA, const RhsScalar* blB, GEBPTraits traits, LhsPacket *A0, RhsPacket *B_0, RhsPacket *B1, RhsPacket *B2, RhsPacket *B3, AccPacket *C0, AccPacket *C1, AccPacket *C2, AccPacket *C3)
1560 {
1561 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 1X4");
1562 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!");
1563 traits.loadLhsUnaligned(&blA[(0+1*K)*(LhsProgress)], *A0);
1564 traits.broadcastRhs(&blB[(0+4*K)*RhsProgress], *B_0, *B1, *B2, *B3);
1565 traits.madd(*A0, *B_0, *C0, *B_0);
1566 traits.madd(*A0, *B1, *C1, *B1);
1567 traits.madd(*A0, *B2, *C2, *B2);
1568 traits.madd(*A0, *B3, *C3, *B3);
1569 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 1X4");
1570 }
1571};

1573template<typename LhsScalar, typename RhsScalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
1574EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
1575void gebp_kernel<LhsScalar,RhsScalar,Index,DataMapper,mr,nr,ConjugateLhs,ConjugateRhs>
1576 ::operator()(const DataMapper& res, const LhsScalar* blockA, const RhsScalar* blockB,
1577 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, ResScalar alpha,
1578 Index strideA, Index strideB, Index offsetA, Index offsetB)
1579 {
1580 Traits traits;
1581 SwappedTraits straits;
1582
1583 if(strideA==-1) strideA = depth;
1584 if(strideB==-1) strideB = depth;
1585 conj_helper<LhsScalar,RhsScalar,ConjugateLhs,ConjugateRhs> cj;
1586 Index packet_cols4 = nr>=4 ? (cols/4) * 4 : 0;
1587 const Index peeled_mc3 = mr>=3*Traits::LhsProgress ? (rows/(3*LhsProgress))*(3*LhsProgress) : 0;
1588 const Index peeled_mc2 = mr>=2*Traits::LhsProgress ? peeled_mc3+((rows-peeled_mc3)/(2*LhsProgress))*(2*LhsProgress) : 0;
1589 const Index peeled_mc1 = mr>=1*Traits::LhsProgress ? peeled_mc2+((rows-peeled_mc2)/(1*LhsProgress))*(1*LhsProgress) : 0;
1590 const Index peeled_mc_half = mr>=LhsProgressHalf ? peeled_mc1+((rows-peeled_mc1)/(LhsProgressHalf))*(LhsProgressHalf) : 0;
1591 const Index peeled_mc_quarter = mr>=LhsProgressQuarter ? peeled_mc_half+((rows-peeled_mc_half)/(LhsProgressQuarter))*(LhsProgressQuarter) : 0;
1592 enum { pk = 8 }; // NOTE Such a large peeling factor is important for large matrices (~ +5% when >1000 on Haswell)
1593 const Index peeled_kc = depth & ~(pk-1);
1594 const int prefetch_res_offset = 32/sizeof(ResScalar);
1595// const Index depth2 = depth & ~1;
1596
1597 //---------- Process 3 * LhsProgress rows at once ----------
1598 // This corresponds to 3*LhsProgress x nr register blocks.
1599 // Usually, make sense only with FMA
1600 if(mr>=3*Traits::LhsProgress)
1601 {
1602 // Here, the general idea is to loop on each largest micro horizontal panel of the lhs (3*Traits::LhsProgress x depth)
1603 // and on each largest micro vertical panel of the rhs (depth * nr).
1604 // Blocking sizes, i.e., 'depth' has been computed so that the micro horizontal panel of the lhs fit in L1.
1605 // However, if depth is too small, we can extend the number of rows of these horizontal panels.
1606 // This actual number of rows is computed as follow:
1607 const Index l1 = defaultL1CacheSize; // in Bytes, TODO, l1 should be passed to this function.
1608 // The max(1, ...) here is needed because we may be using blocking params larger than what our known l1 cache size
1609 // suggests we should be using: either because our known l1 cache size is inaccurate (e.g. on Android, we can only guess),
1610 // or because we are testing specific blocking sizes.
1611 const Index actual_panel_rows = (3*LhsProgress) * std::max<Index>(1,( (l1 - sizeof(ResScalar)*mr*nr - depth*nr*sizeof(RhsScalar)) / (depth * sizeof(LhsScalar) * 3*LhsProgress) ));
1612 for(Index i1=0; i1<peeled_mc3; i1+=actual_panel_rows)
1613 {
1614 const Index actual_panel_end = (std::min)(i1+actual_panel_rows, peeled_mc3);
1615 for(Index j2=0; j2<packet_cols4; j2+=nr)
1616 {
1617 for(Index i=i1; i<actual_panel_end; i+=3*LhsProgress)
1618 {
1619
1620 // We selected a 3*Traits::LhsProgress x nr micro block of res which is entirely
1621 // stored into 3 x nr registers.
1622
1623 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(3*LhsProgress)];
1624 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1625
1626 // gets res block as register
1627 AccPacket C0, C1, C2, C3,
1628 C4, C5, C6, C7,
1629 C8, C9, C10, C11;
1630 traits.initAcc(C0); traits.initAcc(C1); traits.initAcc(C2); traits.initAcc(C3);
1631 traits.initAcc(C4); traits.initAcc(C5); traits.initAcc(C6); traits.initAcc(C7);
1632 traits.initAcc(C8); traits.initAcc(C9); traits.initAcc(C10); traits.initAcc(C11);
1633
1634 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 0);
1635 LinearMapper r1 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 1);
1636 LinearMapper r2 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 2);
1637 LinearMapper r3 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 3);
1638
1639 r0.prefetch(0);
1640 r1.prefetch(0);
1641 r2.prefetch(0);
1642 r3.prefetch(0);
1643
1644 // performs "inner" products
1645 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB*nr];
1646 prefetch(&blB[0]);
1647 LhsPacket A0, A1;
1648
1649 for(Index k=0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
1650 {
1651 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 3pX4");
1652 // 15 registers are taken (12 for acc, 2 for lhs).
1653 RhsPanel15 rhs_panel;
1654 RhsPacket T0;
1655 LhsPacket A2;
1656 #if EIGEN_COMP_GNUC_STRICT && EIGEN_ARCH_ARM64 && defined(EIGEN_VECTORIZE_NEON) && !(EIGEN_GNUC_AT_LEAST(9,0))
1657 // see http://eigen.tuxfamily.org/bz/show_bug.cgi?id=1633
1658 // without this workaround A0, A1, and A2 are loaded in the same register,
1659 // which is not good for pipelining
1660 #define EIGEN_GEBP_3PX4_REGISTER_ALLOC_WORKAROUND __asm__ ("" : "+w,m" (A0), "+w,m" (A1), "+w,m" (A2));
1661 #else
1662 #define EIGEN_GEBP_3PX4_REGISTER_ALLOC_WORKAROUND
1663 #endif
1664#define EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(K) \
1665 do { \
1666 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 3pX4"); \
1667 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!"); \
1668 internal::prefetch(blA + (3 * K + 16) * LhsProgress); \
1669 if (EIGEN_ARCH_ARM || EIGEN_ARCH_MIPS) { \
1670 internal::prefetch(blB + (4 * K + 16) * RhsProgress); \
1671 } /* Bug 953 */ \
1672 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(0 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A0); \
1673 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(1 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A1); \
1674 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(2 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A2); \
1675 EIGEN_GEBP_3PX4_REGISTER_ALLOC_WORKAROUND \
1676 traits.loadRhs(blB + (0+4*K) * Traits::RhsProgress, rhs_panel); \
1677 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C0, T0, fix<0>); \
1678 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C4, T0, fix<0>); \
1679 traits.madd(A2, rhs_panel, C8, T0, fix<0>); \
1680 traits.updateRhs(blB + (1+4*K) * Traits::RhsProgress, rhs_panel); \
1681 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C1, T0, fix<1>); \
1682 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C5, T0, fix<1>); \
1683 traits.madd(A2, rhs_panel, C9, T0, fix<1>); \
1684 traits.updateRhs(blB + (2+4*K) * Traits::RhsProgress, rhs_panel); \
1685 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C2, T0, fix<2>); \
1686 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C6, T0, fix<2>); \
1687 traits.madd(A2, rhs_panel, C10, T0, fix<2>); \
1688 traits.updateRhs(blB + (3+4*K) * Traits::RhsProgress, rhs_panel); \
1689 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C3, T0, fix<3>); \
1690 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C7, T0, fix<3>); \
1691 traits.madd(A2, rhs_panel, C11, T0, fix<3>); \
1692 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 3pX4"); \
1693 } while (false)
1694
1695 internal::prefetch(blB);
1696 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(0);
1697 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(1);
1698 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(2);
1699 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(3);
1700 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(4);
1701 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(5);
1702 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(6);
1703 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(7);
1704
1705 blB += pk*4*RhsProgress;
1706 blA += pk*3*Traits::LhsProgress;
1707
1708 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 3pX4");
1709 }
1710 // process remaining peeled loop
1711 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
1712 {
1713 RhsPanel15 rhs_panel;
1714 RhsPacket T0;
1715 LhsPacket A2;
1716 EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP(0);
1717 blB += 4*RhsProgress;
1718 blA += 3*Traits::LhsProgress;
1719 }
1720
1721#undef EIGEN_GEBP_ONESTEP
1722
1723 ResPacket R0, R1, R2;
1724 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
1725
1726 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1727 R1 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1728 R2 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1729 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
1730 traits.acc(C4, alphav, R1);
1731 traits.acc(C8, alphav, R2);
1732 r0.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1733 r0.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1734 r0.storePacket(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1735
1736 R0 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1737 R1 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1738 R2 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1739 traits.acc(C1, alphav, R0);
1740 traits.acc(C5, alphav, R1);
1741 traits.acc(C9, alphav, R2);
1742 r1.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1743 r1.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1744 r1.storePacket(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1745
1746 R0 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1747 R1 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1748 R2 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1749 traits.acc(C2, alphav, R0);
1750 traits.acc(C6, alphav, R1);
1751 traits.acc(C10, alphav, R2);
1752 r2.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1753 r2.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1754 r2.storePacket(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1755
1756 R0 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1757 R1 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1758 R2 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1759 traits.acc(C3, alphav, R0);
1760 traits.acc(C7, alphav, R1);
1761 traits.acc(C11, alphav, R2);
1762 r3.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1763 r3.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1764 r3.storePacket(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1765 }
1766 }
1767
1768 // Deal with remaining columns of the rhs
1769 for(Index j2=packet_cols4; j2<cols; j2++)
1770 {
1771 for(Index i=i1; i<actual_panel_end; i+=3*LhsProgress)
1772 {
1773 // One column at a time
1774 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(3*Traits::LhsProgress)];
1775 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1776
1777 // gets res block as register
1778 AccPacket C0, C4, C8;
1779 traits.initAcc(C0);
1780 traits.initAcc(C4);
1781 traits.initAcc(C8);
1782
1783 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2);
1784 r0.prefetch(0);
1785
1786 // performs "inner" products
1787 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB];
1788 LhsPacket A0, A1, A2;
1789
1790 for(Index k=0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
1791 {
1792 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 3pX1");
1793 RhsPacket B_0;
1794#define EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(K) \
1795 do { \
1796 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 3pX1"); \
1797 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!"); \
1798 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(0 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A0); \
1799 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(1 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A1); \
1800 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(2 + 3 * K) * LhsProgress], A2); \
1801 traits.loadRhs(&blB[(0 + K) * RhsProgress], B_0); \
1802 traits.madd(A0, B_0, C0, B_0, fix<0>); \
1803 traits.madd(A1, B_0, C4, B_0, fix<0>); \
1804 traits.madd(A2, B_0, C8, B_0, fix<0>); \
1805 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 3pX1"); \
1806 } while (false)
1807
1808 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1809 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(1);
1810 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(2);
1811 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(3);
1812 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(4);
1813 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(5);
1814 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(6);
1815 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(7);
1816
1817 blB += pk*RhsProgress;
1818 blA += pk*3*Traits::LhsProgress;
1819
1820 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 3pX1");
1821 }
1822
1823 // process remaining peeled loop
1824 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
1825 {
1826 RhsPacket B_0;
1827 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1828 blB += RhsProgress;
1829 blA += 3*Traits::LhsProgress;
1830 }
1831#undef EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP
1832 ResPacket R0, R1, R2;
1833 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
1834
1835 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1836 R1 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1837 R2 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1838 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
1839 traits.acc(C4, alphav, R1);
1840 traits.acc(C8, alphav, R2);
1841 r0.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1842 r0.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1843 r0.storePacket(2 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1844 }
1845 }
1846 }
1847 }
1848
1849 //---------- Process 2 * LhsProgress rows at once ----------
1850 if(mr>=2*Traits::LhsProgress)
1851 {
1852 const Index l1 = defaultL1CacheSize; // in Bytes, TODO, l1 should be passed to this function.
1853 // The max(1, ...) here is needed because we may be using blocking params larger than what our known l1 cache size
1854 // suggests we should be using: either because our known l1 cache size is inaccurate (e.g. on Android, we can only guess),
1855 // or because we are testing specific blocking sizes.
1856 Index actual_panel_rows = (2*LhsProgress) * std::max<Index>(1,( (l1 - sizeof(ResScalar)*mr*nr - depth*nr*sizeof(RhsScalar)) / (depth * sizeof(LhsScalar) * 2*LhsProgress) ));
1857
1858 for(Index i1=peeled_mc3; i1<peeled_mc2; i1+=actual_panel_rows)
1859 {
1860 Index actual_panel_end = (std::min)(i1+actual_panel_rows, peeled_mc2);
1861 for(Index j2=0; j2<packet_cols4; j2+=nr)
1862 {
1863 for(Index i=i1; i<actual_panel_end; i+=2*LhsProgress)
1864 {
1865
1866 // We selected a 2*Traits::LhsProgress x nr micro block of res which is entirely
1867 // stored into 2 x nr registers.
1868
1869 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(2*Traits::LhsProgress)];
1870 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1871
1872 // gets res block as register
1873 AccPacket C0, C1, C2, C3,
1874 C4, C5, C6, C7;
1875 traits.initAcc(C0); traits.initAcc(C1); traits.initAcc(C2); traits.initAcc(C3);
1876 traits.initAcc(C4); traits.initAcc(C5); traits.initAcc(C6); traits.initAcc(C7);
1877
1878 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 0);
1879 LinearMapper r1 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 1);
1880 LinearMapper r2 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 2);
1881 LinearMapper r3 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2 + 3);
1882
1883 r0.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1884 r1.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1885 r2.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1886 r3.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1887
1888 // performs "inner" products
1889 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB*nr];
1890 prefetch(&blB[0]);
1891 LhsPacket A0, A1;
1892
1893 for(Index k=0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
1894 {
1895 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 2pX4");
1896 RhsPacketx4 rhs_panel;
1897 RhsPacket T0;
1898
1899 // NOTE: the begin/end asm comments below work around bug 935!
1900 // but they are not enough for gcc>=6 without FMA (bug 1637)
1901 #if EIGEN_GNUC_AT_LEAST(6,0) && defined(EIGEN_VECTORIZE_SSE)
1902 #define EIGEN_GEBP_2PX4_SPILLING_WORKAROUND __asm__ ("" : [a0] "+x,m" (A0),[a1] "+x,m" (A1));
1903 #else
1904 #define EIGEN_GEBP_2PX4_SPILLING_WORKAROUND
1905 #endif
1906#define EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(K) \
1907 do { \
1908 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 2pX4"); \
1909 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(0 + 2 * K) * LhsProgress], A0); \
1910 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(1 + 2 * K) * LhsProgress], A1); \
1911 traits.loadRhs(&blB[(0 + 4 * K) * RhsProgress], rhs_panel); \
1912 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C0, T0, fix<0>); \
1913 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C4, T0, fix<0>); \
1914 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C1, T0, fix<1>); \
1915 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C5, T0, fix<1>); \
1916 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C2, T0, fix<2>); \
1917 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C6, T0, fix<2>); \
1918 traits.madd(A0, rhs_panel, C3, T0, fix<3>); \
1919 traits.madd(A1, rhs_panel, C7, T0, fix<3>); \
1920 EIGEN_GEBP_2PX4_SPILLING_WORKAROUND \
1921 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 2pX4"); \
1922 } while (false)
1923
1924 internal::prefetch(blB+(48+0));
1925 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1926 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(1);
1927 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(2);
1928 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(3);
1929 internal::prefetch(blB+(48+16));
1930 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(4);
1931 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(5);
1932 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(6);
1933 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(7);
1934
1935 blB += pk*4*RhsProgress;
1936 blA += pk*(2*Traits::LhsProgress);
1937
1938 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 2pX4");
1939 }
1940 // process remaining peeled loop
1941 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
1942 {
1943 RhsPacketx4 rhs_panel;
1944 RhsPacket T0;
1945 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
1946 blB += 4*RhsProgress;
1947 blA += 2*Traits::LhsProgress;
1948 }
1949#undef EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP
1950
1951 ResPacket R0, R1, R2, R3;
1952 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
1953
1954 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1955 R1 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1956 R2 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1957 R3 = r1.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1958 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
1959 traits.acc(C4, alphav, R1);
1960 traits.acc(C1, alphav, R2);
1961 traits.acc(C5, alphav, R3);
1962 r0.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1963 r0.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1964 r1.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1965 r1.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R3);
1966
1967 R0 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1968 R1 = r2.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1969 R2 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1970 R3 = r3.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
1971 traits.acc(C2, alphav, R0);
1972 traits.acc(C6, alphav, R1);
1973 traits.acc(C3, alphav, R2);
1974 traits.acc(C7, alphav, R3);
1975 r2.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
1976 r2.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
1977 r3.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R2);
1978 r3.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R3);
1979 }
1980 }
1981
1982 // Deal with remaining columns of the rhs
1983 for(Index j2=packet_cols4; j2<cols; j2++)
1984 {
1985 for(Index i=i1; i<actual_panel_end; i+=2*LhsProgress)
1986 {
1987 // One column at a time
1988 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA*(2*Traits::LhsProgress)];
1989 prefetch(&blA[0]);
1990
1991 // gets res block as register
1992 AccPacket C0, C4;
1993 traits.initAcc(C0);
1994 traits.initAcc(C4);
1995
1996 LinearMapper r0 = res.getLinearMapper(i, j2);
1997 r0.prefetch(prefetch_res_offset);
1998
1999 // performs "inner" products
2000 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB];
2001 LhsPacket A0, A1;
2002
2003 for(Index k=0; k<peeled_kc; k+=pk)
2004 {
2005 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin gebp micro kernel 2pX1");
2006 RhsPacket B_0, B1;
2007
2008#define EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(K) \
2009 do { \
2010 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("begin step of gebp micro kernel 2pX1"); \
2011 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("Note: these asm comments work around bug 935!"); \
2012 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(0+2*K)*LhsProgress], A0); \
2013 traits.loadLhs(&blA[(1+2*K)*LhsProgress], A1); \
2014 traits.loadRhs(&blB[(0+K)*RhsProgress], B_0); \
2015 traits.madd(A0, B_0, C0, B1, fix<0>); \
2016 traits.madd(A1, B_0, C4, B_0, fix<0>); \
2017 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end step of gebp micro kernel 2pX1"); \
2018 } while(false)
2019
2020 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
2021 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(1);
2022 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(2);
2023 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(3);
2024 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(4);
2025 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(5);
2026 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(6);
2027 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(7);
2028
2029 blB += pk*RhsProgress;
2030 blA += pk*2*Traits::LhsProgress;
2031
2032 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("end gebp micro kernel 2pX1");
2033 }
2034
2035 // process remaining peeled loop
2036 for(Index k=peeled_kc; k<depth; k++)
2037 {
2038 RhsPacket B_0, B1;
2039 EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP(0);
2040 blB += RhsProgress;
2041 blA += 2*Traits::LhsProgress;
2042 }
2043#undef EIGEN_GEBGP_ONESTEP
2044 ResPacket R0, R1;
2045 ResPacket alphav = pset1<ResPacket>(alpha);
2046
2047 R0 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
2048 R1 = r0.template loadPacket<ResPacket>(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize);
2049 traits.acc(C0, alphav, R0);
2050 traits.acc(C4, alphav, R1);
2051 r0.storePacket(0 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R0);
2052 r0.storePacket(1 * Traits::ResPacketSize, R1);
2053 }
2054 }
2055 }
2056 }
2057 //---------- Process 1 * LhsProgress rows at once ----------
2058 if(mr>=1*Traits::LhsProgress)
2059 {
2060 lhs_process_one_packet<nr, LhsProgress, RhsProgress, LhsScalar, RhsScalar, ResScalar, AccPacket, LhsPacket, RhsPacket, ResPacket, Traits, LinearMapper, DataMapper> p;
2061 p(res, blockA, blockB, alpha, peeled_mc2, peeled_mc1, strideA, strideB, offsetA, offsetB, prefetch_res_offset, peeled_kc, pk, cols, depth, packet_cols4);
2062 }
2063 //---------- Process LhsProgressHalf rows at once ----------
2064 if((LhsProgressHalf < LhsProgress) && mr>=LhsProgressHalf)
2065 {
2066 lhs_process_fraction_of_packet<nr, LhsProgressHalf, RhsProgressHalf, LhsScalar, RhsScalar, ResScalar, AccPacketHalf, LhsPacketHalf, RhsPacketHalf, ResPacketHalf, HalfTraits, LinearMapper, DataMapper> p;
2067 p(res, blockA, blockB, alpha, peeled_mc1, peeled_mc_half, strideA, strideB, offsetA, offsetB, prefetch_res_offset, peeled_kc, pk, cols, depth, packet_cols4);
2068 }
2069 //---------- Process LhsProgressQuarter rows at once ----------
2070 if((LhsProgressQuarter < LhsProgressHalf) && mr>=LhsProgressQuarter)
2071 {
2072 lhs_process_fraction_of_packet<nr, LhsProgressQuarter, RhsProgressQuarter, LhsScalar, RhsScalar, ResScalar, AccPacketQuarter, LhsPacketQuarter, RhsPacketQuarter, ResPacketQuarter, QuarterTraits, LinearMapper, DataMapper> p;
2073 p(res, blockA, blockB, alpha, peeled_mc_half, peeled_mc_quarter, strideA, strideB, offsetA, offsetB, prefetch_res_offset, peeled_kc, pk, cols, depth, packet_cols4);
2074 }
2075 //---------- Process remaining rows, 1 at once ----------
2076 if(peeled_mc_quarter<rows)
2077 {
2078 // loop on each panel of the rhs
2079 for(Index j2=0; j2<packet_cols4; j2+=nr)
2080 {
2081 // loop on each row of the lhs (1*LhsProgress x depth)
2082 for(Index i=peeled_mc_quarter; i<rows; i+=1)
2083 {
2084 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA];
2085 prefetch(&blA[0]);
2086 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB*nr];
2087
2088 // If LhsProgress is 8 or 16, it assumes that there is a
2089 // half or quarter packet, respectively, of the same size as
2090 // nr (which is currently 4) for the return type.
2091 const int SResPacketHalfSize = unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SResPacket>::half>::size;
2092 const int SResPacketQuarterSize = unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<SResPacket>::half>::half>::size;
2093 if ((SwappedTraits::LhsProgress % 4) == 0 &&
2094 (SwappedTraits::LhsProgress<=16) &&
2095 (SwappedTraits::LhsProgress!=8 || SResPacketHalfSize==nr) &&
2096 (SwappedTraits::LhsProgress!=16 || SResPacketQuarterSize==nr))
2097 {
2098 SAccPacket C0, C1, C2, C3;
2099 straits.initAcc(C0);
2100 straits.initAcc(C1);
2101 straits.initAcc(C2);
2102 straits.initAcc(C3);
2103
2104 const Index spk = (std::max)(1,SwappedTraits::LhsProgress/4);
2105 const Index endk = (depth/spk)*spk;
2106 const Index endk4 = (depth/(spk*4))*(spk*4);
2107
2108 Index k=0;
2109 for(; k<endk4; k+=4*spk)
2110 {
2111 SLhsPacket A0,A1;
2112 SRhsPacket B_0,B_1;
2113
2114 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB+0*SwappedTraits::LhsProgress, A0);
2115 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB+1*SwappedTraits::LhsProgress, A1);
2116
2117 straits.loadRhsQuad(blA+0*spk, B_0);
2118 straits.loadRhsQuad(blA+1*spk, B_1);
2119 straits.madd(A0,B_0,C0,B_0, fix<0>);
2120 straits.madd(A1,B_1,C1,B_1, fix<0>);
2121
2122 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB+2*SwappedTraits::LhsProgress, A0);
2123 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB+3*SwappedTraits::LhsProgress, A1);
2124 straits.loadRhsQuad(blA+2*spk, B_0);
2125 straits.loadRhsQuad(blA+3*spk, B_1);
2126 straits.madd(A0,B_0,C2,B_0, fix<0>);
2127 straits.madd(A1,B_1,C3,B_1, fix<0>);
2128
2129 blB += 4*SwappedTraits::LhsProgress;
2130 blA += 4*spk;
2131 }
2132 C0 = padd(padd(C0,C1),padd(C2,C3));
2133 for(; k<endk; k+=spk)
2134 {
2135 SLhsPacket A0;
2136 SRhsPacket B_0;
2137
2138 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB, A0);
2139 straits.loadRhsQuad(blA, B_0);
2140 straits.madd(A0,B_0,C0,B_0, fix<0>);
2141
2142 blB += SwappedTraits::LhsProgress;
2143 blA += spk;
2144 }
2145 if(SwappedTraits::LhsProgress==8)
2146 {
2147 // Special case where we have to first reduce the accumulation register C0
2148 typedef typename conditional<SwappedTraits::LhsProgress>=8,typename unpacket_traits<SResPacket>::half,SResPacket>::type SResPacketHalf;
2149 typedef typename conditional<SwappedTraits::LhsProgress>=8,typename unpacket_traits<SLhsPacket>::half,SLhsPacket>::type SLhsPacketHalf;
2150 typedef typename conditional<SwappedTraits::LhsProgress>=8,typename unpacket_traits<SRhsPacket>::half,SRhsPacket>::type SRhsPacketHalf;
2151 typedef typename conditional<SwappedTraits::LhsProgress>=8,typename unpacket_traits<SAccPacket>::half,SAccPacket>::type SAccPacketHalf;
2152
2153 SResPacketHalf R = res.template gatherPacket<SResPacketHalf>(i, j2);
2154 SResPacketHalf alphav = pset1<SResPacketHalf>(alpha);
2155
2156 if(depth-endk>0)
2157 {
2158 // We have to handle the last row of the rhs which corresponds to a half-packet
2159 SLhsPacketHalf a0;
2160 SRhsPacketHalf b0;
2161 straits.loadLhsUnaligned(blB, a0);
2162 straits.loadRhs(blA, b0);
2163 SAccPacketHalf c0 = predux_half_dowto4(C0);
2164 straits.madd(a0,b0,c0,b0, fix<0>);
2165 straits.acc(c0, alphav, R);
2166 }
2167 else
2168 {
2169 straits.acc(predux_half_dowto4(C0), alphav, R);
2170 }
2171 res.scatterPacket(i, j2, R);
2172 }
2173 else if (SwappedTraits::LhsProgress==16)
2174 {
2175 // Special case where we have to first reduce the
2176 // accumulation register C0. We specialize the block in
2177 // template form, so that LhsProgress < 16 paths don't
2178 // fail to compile
2179 last_row_process_16_packets<LhsScalar, RhsScalar, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs> p;
2180 p(res, straits, blA, blB, depth, endk, i, j2,alpha, C0);
2181 }
2182 else
2183 {
2184 SResPacket R = res.template gatherPacket<SResPacket>(i, j2);
2185 SResPacket alphav = pset1<SResPacket>(alpha);
2186 straits.acc(C0, alphav, R);
2187 res.scatterPacket(i, j2, R);
2188 }
2189 }
2190 else // scalar path
2191 {
2192 // get a 1 x 4 res block as registers
2193 ResScalar C0(0), C1(0), C2(0), C3(0);
2194
2195 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2196 {
2197 LhsScalar A0;
2198 RhsScalar B_0, B_1;
2199
2200 A0 = blA[k];
2201
2202 B_0 = blB[0];
2203 B_1 = blB[1];
2204 CJMADD(cj,A0,B_0,C0, B_0);
2205 CJMADD(cj,A0,B_1,C1, B_1);
2206
2207 B_0 = blB[2];
2208 B_1 = blB[3];
2209 CJMADD(cj,A0,B_0,C2, B_0);
2210 CJMADD(cj,A0,B_1,C3, B_1);
2211
2212 blB += 4;
2213 }
2214 res(i, j2 + 0) += alpha * C0;
2215 res(i, j2 + 1) += alpha * C1;
2216 res(i, j2 + 2) += alpha * C2;
2217 res(i, j2 + 3) += alpha * C3;
2218 }
2219 }
2220 }
2221 // remaining columns
2222 for(Index j2=packet_cols4; j2<cols; j2++)
2223 {
2224 // loop on each row of the lhs (1*LhsProgress x depth)
2225 for(Index i=peeled_mc_quarter; i<rows; i+=1)
2226 {
2227 const LhsScalar* blA = &blockA[i*strideA+offsetA];
2228 prefetch(&blA[0]);
2229 // gets a 1 x 1 res block as registers
2230 ResScalar C0(0);
2231 const RhsScalar* blB = &blockB[j2*strideB+offsetB];
2232 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2233 {
2234 LhsScalar A0 = blA[k];
2235 RhsScalar B_0 = blB[k];
2236 CJMADD(cj, A0, B_0, C0, B_0);
2237 }
2238 res(i, j2) += alpha * C0;
2239 }
2240 }
2241 }
2242 }
2243
2244
2245#undef CJMADD

2247// pack a block of the lhs
2248// The traversal is as follow (mr==4):
2249// 0 4 8 12 ...
2250// 1 5 9 13 ...
2251// 2 6 10 14 ...
2252// 3 7 11 15 ...
2253//
2254// 16 20 24 28 ...
2255// 17 21 25 29 ...
2256// 18 22 26 30 ...
2257// 19 23 27 31 ...
2258//
2259// 32 33 34 35 ...
2260// 36 36 38 39 ...
2261template<typename Scalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2, typename Packet, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
2262struct gemm_pack_lhs<Scalar, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, Packet, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>
2263{
2264 typedef typename DataMapper::LinearMapper LinearMapper;
2265 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(Scalar* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows, Index stride=0, Index offset=0);
2266};

2268template<typename Scalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2, typename Packet, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
2269EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_lhs<Scalar, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, Packet, ColMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>
2270 ::operator()(Scalar* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows, Index stride, Index offset)
2271{
2272 typedef typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half HalfPacket;
2273 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half>::half QuarterPacket;
2274 enum { PacketSize = unpacket_traits<Packet>::size,
2275 HalfPacketSize = unpacket_traits<HalfPacket>::size,
2276 QuarterPacketSize = unpacket_traits<QuarterPacket>::size,
2277 HasHalf = (int)HalfPacketSize < (int)PacketSize,
2278 HasQuarter = (int)QuarterPacketSize < (int)HalfPacketSize};
2279
2280 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("EIGEN PRODUCT PACK LHS");
2281 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(stride);
2282 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(offset);
2283 eigen_assert(((!PanelMode) && stride==0 && offset==0) || (PanelMode && stride>=depth && offset<=stride));
2284 eigen_assert( ((Pack1%PacketSize)==0 && Pack1<=4*PacketSize) || (Pack1<=4) );
2285 conj_if<NumTraits<Scalar>::IsComplex && Conjugate> cj;
2286 Index count = 0;
2287
2288 const Index peeled_mc3 = Pack1>=3*PacketSize ? (rows/(3*PacketSize))*(3*PacketSize) : 0;
2289 const Index peeled_mc2 = Pack1>=2*PacketSize ? peeled_mc3+((rows-peeled_mc3)/(2*PacketSize))*(2*PacketSize) : 0;
2290 const Index peeled_mc1 = Pack1>=1*PacketSize ? peeled_mc2+((rows-peeled_mc2)/(1*PacketSize))*(1*PacketSize) : 0;
2291 const Index peeled_mc_half = Pack1>=HalfPacketSize ? peeled_mc1+((rows-peeled_mc1)/(HalfPacketSize))*(HalfPacketSize) : 0;
2292 const Index peeled_mc_quarter = Pack1>=QuarterPacketSize ? (rows/(QuarterPacketSize))*(QuarterPacketSize) : 0;
2293 const Index last_lhs_progress = rows > peeled_mc_quarter ? (rows - peeled_mc_quarter) & ~1 : 0;
2294 const Index peeled_mc0 = Pack2>=PacketSize ? peeled_mc_quarter
2295 : Pack2>1 && last_lhs_progress ? (rows/last_lhs_progress)*last_lhs_progress : 0;
2296
2297 Index i=0;
2298
2299 // Pack 3 packets
2300 if(Pack1>=3*PacketSize)
2301 {
2302 for(; i<peeled_mc3; i+=3*PacketSize)
2303 {
2304 if(PanelMode) count += (3*PacketSize) * offset;
2305
2306 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2307 {
2308 Packet A, B, C;
2309 A = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+0*PacketSize, k);
2310 B = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+1*PacketSize, k);
2311 C = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+2*PacketSize, k);
2312 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(A)); count+=PacketSize;
2313 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(B)); count+=PacketSize;
2314 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(C)); count+=PacketSize;
2315 }
2316 if(PanelMode) count += (3*PacketSize) * (stride-offset-depth);
2317 }
2318 }
2319 // Pack 2 packets
2320 if(Pack1>=2*PacketSize)
2321 {
2322 for(; i<peeled_mc2; i+=2*PacketSize)
2323 {
2324 if(PanelMode) count += (2*PacketSize) * offset;
2325
2326 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2327 {
2328 Packet A, B;
2329 A = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+0*PacketSize, k);
2330 B = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+1*PacketSize, k);
2331 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(A)); count+=PacketSize;
2332 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(B)); count+=PacketSize;
2333 }
2334 if(PanelMode) count += (2*PacketSize) * (stride-offset-depth);
2335 }
2336 }
2337 // Pack 1 packets
2338 if(Pack1>=1*PacketSize)
2339 {
2340 for(; i<peeled_mc1; i+=1*PacketSize)
2341 {
2342 if(PanelMode) count += (1*PacketSize) * offset;
2343
2344 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2345 {
2346 Packet A;
2347 A = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+0*PacketSize, k);
2348 pstore(blockA+count, cj.pconj(A));
2349 count+=PacketSize;
2350 }
2351 if(PanelMode) count += (1*PacketSize) * (stride-offset-depth);
2352 }
2353 }
2354 // Pack half packets
2355 if(HasHalf && Pack1>=HalfPacketSize)
2356 {
2357 for(; i<peeled_mc_half; i+=HalfPacketSize)
2358 {
2359 if(PanelMode) count += (HalfPacketSize) * offset;
2360
2361 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2362 {
2363 HalfPacket A;
2364 A = lhs.template loadPacket<HalfPacket>(i+0*(HalfPacketSize), k);
2365 pstoreu(blockA+count, cj.pconj(A));
2366 count+=HalfPacketSize;
2367 }
2368 if(PanelMode) count += (HalfPacketSize) * (stride-offset-depth);
2369 }
2370 }
2371 // Pack quarter packets
2372 if(HasQuarter && Pack1>=QuarterPacketSize)
2373 {
2374 for(; i<peeled_mc_quarter; i+=QuarterPacketSize)
2375 {
2376 if(PanelMode) count += (QuarterPacketSize) * offset;
2377
2378 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2379 {
2380 QuarterPacket A;
2381 A = lhs.template loadPacket<QuarterPacket>(i+0*(QuarterPacketSize), k);
2382 pstoreu(blockA+count, cj.pconj(A));
2383 count+=QuarterPacketSize;
2384 }
2385 if(PanelMode) count += (QuarterPacketSize) * (stride-offset-depth);
2386 }
2387 }
2388 // Pack2 may be *smaller* than PacketSize—that happens for
2389 // products like real * complex, where we have to go half the
2390 // progress on the lhs in order to duplicate those operands to
2391 // address both real & imaginary parts on the rhs. This portion will
2392 // pack those half ones until they match the number expected on the
2393 // last peeling loop at this point (for the rhs).
2394 if(Pack2<PacketSize && Pack2>1)
2395 {
2396 for(; i<peeled_mc0; i+=last_lhs_progress)
2397 {
2398 if(PanelMode) count += last_lhs_progress * offset;
2399
2400 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2401 for(Index w=0; w<last_lhs_progress; w++)
2402 blockA[count++] = cj(lhs(i+w, k));
2403
2404 if(PanelMode) count += last_lhs_progress * (stride-offset-depth);
2405 }
2406 }
2407 // Pack scalars
2408 for(; i<rows; i++)
2409 {
2410 if(PanelMode) count += offset;
2411 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2412 blockA[count++] = cj(lhs(i, k));
2413 if(PanelMode) count += (stride-offset-depth);
2414 }
2415}

2417template<typename Scalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2, typename Packet, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
2418struct gemm_pack_lhs<Scalar, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, Packet, RowMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>
2419{
2420 typedef typename DataMapper::LinearMapper LinearMapper;
2421 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void operator()(Scalar* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows, Index stride=0, Index offset=0);
2422};

2424template<typename Scalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int Pack1, int Pack2, typename Packet, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
2425EIGEN_DONT_INLINE void gemm_pack_lhs<Scalar, Index, DataMapper, Pack1, Pack2, Packet, RowMajor, Conjugate, PanelMode>
2426 ::operator()(Scalar* blockA, const DataMapper& lhs, Index depth, Index rows, Index stride, Index offset)
2427{
2428 typedef typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half HalfPacket;
2429 typedef typename unpacket_traits<typename unpacket_traits<Packet>::half>::half QuarterPacket;
2430 enum { PacketSize = unpacket_traits<Packet>::size,
2431 HalfPacketSize = unpacket_traits<HalfPacket>::size,
2432 QuarterPacketSize = unpacket_traits<QuarterPacket>::size,
2433 HasHalf = (int)HalfPacketSize < (int)PacketSize,
2434 HasQuarter = (int)QuarterPacketSize < (int)HalfPacketSize};
2435
2436 EIGEN_ASM_COMMENT("EIGEN PRODUCT PACK LHS");
2437 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(stride);
2438 EIGEN_UNUSED_VARIABLE(offset);
2439 eigen_assert(((!PanelMode) && stride==0 && offset==0) || (PanelMode && stride>=depth && offset<=stride));
2440 conj_if<NumTraits<Scalar>::IsComplex && Conjugate> cj;
2441 Index count = 0;
2442 bool gone_half = false, gone_quarter = false, gone_last = false;
2443
2444 Index i = 0;
2445 int pack = Pack1;
2446 int psize = PacketSize;
2447 while(pack>0)
2448 {
2449 Index remaining_rows = rows-i;
2450 Index peeled_mc = gone_last ? Pack2>1 ? (rows/pack)*pack : 0 : i+(remaining_rows/pack)*pack;
2451 Index starting_pos = i;
2452 for(; i<peeled_mc; i+=pack)
2453 {
2454 if(PanelMode) count += pack * offset;
2455
2456 Index k=0;
2457 if(pack>=psize && psize >= QuarterPacketSize)
2458 {
2459 const Index peeled_k = (depth/psize)*psize;
2460 for(; k<peeled_k; k+=psize)
2461 {
2462 for (Index m = 0; m < pack; m += psize)
2463 {
2464 if (psize == PacketSize) {
2465 PacketBlock<Packet> kernel;
2466 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) kernel.packet[p] = lhs.template loadPacket<Packet>(i+p+m, k);
2467 ptranspose(kernel);
2468 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) pstore(blockA+count+m+(pack)*p, cj.pconj(kernel.packet[p]));
2469 } else if (HasHalf && psize == HalfPacketSize) {
2470 gone_half = true;
2471 PacketBlock<HalfPacket> kernel_half;
2472 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) kernel_half.packet[p] = lhs.template loadPacket<HalfPacket>(i+p+m, k);
2473 ptranspose(kernel_half);
2474 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) pstore(blockA+count+m+(pack)*p, cj.pconj(kernel_half.packet[p]));
2475 } else if (HasQuarter && psize == QuarterPacketSize) {
2476 gone_quarter = true;
2477 PacketBlock<QuarterPacket> kernel_quarter;
2478 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) kernel_quarter.packet[p] = lhs.template loadPacket<QuarterPacket>(i+p+m, k);
2479 ptranspose(kernel_quarter);
2480 for (int p = 0; p < psize; ++p) pstore(blockA+count+m+(pack)*p, cj.pconj(kernel_quarter.packet[p]));
2481 }
2482 }
2483 count += psize*pack;
2484 }
2485 }
2486
2487 for(; k<depth; k++)
2488 {
2489 Index w=0;
2490 for(; w<pack-3; w+=4)
2491 {
2492 Scalar a(cj(lhs(i+w+0, k))),
2493 b(cj(lhs(i+w+1, k))),
2494 c(cj(lhs(i+w+2, k))),
2495 d(cj(lhs(i+w+3, k)));
2496 blockA[count++] = a;
2497 blockA[count++] = b;
2498 blockA[count++] = c;
2499 blockA[count++] = d;
2500 }
2501 if(pack%4)
2502 for(;w<pack;++w)
2503 blockA[count++] = cj(lhs(i+w, k));
2504 }
2505
2506 if(PanelMode) count += pack * (stride-offset-depth);
2507 }
2508
2509 pack -= psize;
2510 Index left = rows - i;
2511 if (pack <= 0) {
2512 if (!gone_last &&
2513 (starting_pos == i || left >= psize/2 || left >= psize/4) &&
2514 ((psize/2 == HalfPacketSize && HasHalf && !gone_half) ||
2515 (psize/2 == QuarterPacketSize && HasQuarter && !gone_quarter))) {
2516 psize /= 2;
2517 pack = psize;
2518 continue;
2519 }
2520 // Pack2 may be *smaller* than PacketSize—that happens for
2521 // products like real * complex, where we have to go half the
2522 // progress on the lhs in order to duplicate those operands to
2523 // address both real & imaginary parts on the rhs. This portion will
2524 // pack those half ones until they match the number expected on the
2525 // last peeling loop at this point (for the rhs).
2526 if (Pack2 < PacketSize && !gone_last) {
2527 gone_last = true;
2528 psize = pack = left & ~1;
2529 }
2530 }
2531 }
2532
2533 for(; i<rows; i++)
2534 {
2535 if(PanelMode) count += offset;
2536 for(Index k=0; k<depth; k++)
2537 blockA[count++] = cj(lhs(i, k));
2538 if(PanelMode) count += (stride-offset-depth);
2539 }
2540}

2542// copy a complete panel of the rhs
2543// this version is optimized for column major matrices
2544// The traversal order is as follow: (nr==4):
2545// 0 1 2 3 12 13 14 15 24 27
2546// 4 5 6 7 16 17 18 19 25 28
2547// 8 9 10 11 20 21 22 23 26 29
2548// . . . . . . . . . .
2549template<typename Scalar, typename Index, typename DataMapper, int nr, bool Conjugate, bool PanelMode>
